## Ingredients
- 500g potatoes, boiled and mashed
- 1 tsp ginger, grated
- 1 tsp cumin seeds
- 1 tsp garam masala
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 small onion, finely chopped
- 2 green chillies, finely chopped
- 2 tbsp fresh coriander, chopped
- 2-3 tbsp oil, for frying

## Method
1. In a large bowl, combine the mashed potatoes, chopped onion, green chillies, ginger, cumin seeds, garam masala, coriander, and salt.
2. Mix thoroughly until all ingredients are well combined.
3. Divide the mixture into equal portions and shape each portion into a round patty.
4. Heat the oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
5. Fry the patties for about 4-5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
6. Remove from the pan and drain on kitchen paper before serving.

## Notes
- Add breadcrumbs to the mixture for extra crunch.
- These can be made ahead and frozen; just fry from frozen for a quick snack.
- Serve with mint chutney or a tangy tamarind sauce for added flavour.
- Adjust the spices according to your heat preference.
